place.name: STAINTON LE VALE
place.gazetteerText: STAINTON-LE-VALE, a parish in Caistor district, Lincoln; 5½ miles NE of Market-Rasen r. station. Post town, Market-Rasen. Acres, 3,450. Real property, £3,454. Pop., 191. Houses, 35. The manor belongs to W. Angerstein, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £99.* Patron, W. Angerstein, Esq. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
